  "text": "Stigma was assessed using a modified version of the original 10-item generic stigma consciousness questionnaire for gay men and lesbians. [CITATION_1] The questionnaire was shortened and modified by only using four items and by changing the wording from ''homophobic'' to ''transphobic,'' from ''heterosexual'' to ''cisgender,'' and from ''homosexual'' to ''trans.'' Respondents were asked to rate on a seven-grade scale their level of agreement (0 = strongly disagree to 6 = strongly agree) with the following statements: (1) ''Stereotypes about trans people have not affected me personally''; (2) ''I almost never think about the fact that I am trans when I interact with cisgender people''; (3) ''My being trans does not influence how people act toward me''; and (4) ''Most cisgender people have a lot more transphobic thoughts than they actually express.'' Items 1, 2 and 3 received reverse scores. Higher scores indicated higher levels of stigma consciousness.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "393337"
